entries.title: Biden vows to take on the 'plague' of fentanyl as AMLO bemoans 'abandonment' of Latin America
entries.description: Mexican President Andres Manuel Lopez Obrador complained during a meeting with President Biden in Mexico City about 'disdain' for the region, prompting pushback.

entries.title: Joshua Murrell takes selfie with thousands of stolen bras, undies as he poses with gun in Melbourne
entries.description: This is the moment depraved underwear thief Joshua Murrell proudly showed off his imitation firearm while sitting on a bed blanketed with dozens of pairs of women's undies.

entries.title: Brexit deal over Northern Ireland moves a step closer as UK offers trade data to EU
entries.description: The UK said the EU would be given access to data on the flow of goods from mainland Britain to Northern Ireland. It is considered a 'basis' for resolving the long row over Northern Ireland Protocol.

entries.title: Brace for fresh drought this summer as experts warn
entries.description: Despite recent downpours, most of England is 'still in drought', the Environment Agency explains. Another drought is expected this summer unless there is exceptional rainfall in coming months.

entries.title: Adelaide disabled woman in a wheelchair is dragged off train as South Australia Police defend cops
entries.description: Shocking footage taken last Saturday showed the woman being forced off of the Adelaide Metro service and onto the platform.

entries.title: Fight against inflation is not over yet, bank chief says
entries.description: Signalling that he favours yet more interest rate hikes, Huw Pill warned that even as energy prices stabilised, staff shortages and supply chain problems meant inflation could 'prove more persistent'.

entries.title: Harmony of the Seas pool turns into a waterfall after ship makes hard turn to avoid raft in the sea
entries.description: Passengers aboard the Harmony of the Seas experienced an unexpected waterfall after the ship did a hard-turn to avoid a raft in the sea and water from a pool began spilling onto a lower deck.

entries.title: Man, 19, identified as speeding motorcyclist who fled cops taking them on a wild high-speed chase
entries.description: Charles Reid Roseberry, 19, of Riverdale, Georgia has been identified as the speeding motorcyclist who took police on a wild high-speed chase through two counties in Georgia.

entries.title: Buckingham Palace advertises for £34,000-a-year helicopter operations officer
entries.description: The role comes with an advertised salary of £34,000, depending on experience, and requires flexibility to work outside of office hours.

entries.title: Model dressed as 'sexy nun' is confronted at St Mary's Cathedral in Sydney during photoshoot
entries.description: Charlie Bakhos had been at St Mary's Cathedral in Sydney's CBD on Monday when he spotted a woman scantily clad in lingerie, knee-high white socks, high heels and a nun's habit.

entries.title: Vegan group promises £1million donation to charity... if Rishi Sunak takes up plant-based diet
entries.description: Generation Vegan (GenV) has urged the Prime Minister to 'consider our sincere offer and lead the UK towards a more sustainable and promising future'.

entries.title: Strike ballots for teachers will go ahead after talks over pay broke down
entries.description: The talks with Education Secretary Gillian Keegan were described as 'largely unsatisfactory' by school leaders with concerns over pay and teacher shortages 'remaining unresolved'.

entries.title: Tiger snakes on Mount Chappell Island, Tasmania, mutate to be twice as big, more venomous
entries.description: The island of Mount Chappell, just off the coast of Tasmania, is said to be home to Australia's largest and most venomous tiger snakes who hunt birds and have made the island their own.

entries.title: Chicago attorney apologizes after calling deputies 'those motherf*****' and using racial slur
entries.description: Donna Makowski groveled before a judge at a contempt of court hearing Friday after she was caught on camera saying 'Those motherf****** at the sheriff's office' and 'N****** do it all the time.'

entries.title: New House GOP majority PASSES rules package with only one Republican defection
entries.description: The House of Representatives passed a rules package Monday night 220-213 with relatively little drama as the first order of business for House Speaker Kevin McCarthy's new majority.

entries.title: Even US media turns on Prince Harry with New York Times calling his words 'repetitive and tiresome'
entries.description: It may come as a surprise to learn that even the Left-wing US newspaper The New York Times has run an article suggesting that Americans may be tiring of Prince Harry's complaints.

entries.title: Royal family have 'no trust left' for Prince Harry after Spare bombshells and TV interviews
entries.description: After the onslaught of bombshells the Duke of Sussex dropped this week, his father and brother are reportedly at their wits end.

entries.title: Police manhunt after woman attacked by man hiding in bushes at Quinns Dog Beach, Western Australia
entries.description: Police are on the hunt for a man who jumped out of bushes  and tried to drag a young woman into bushland in a terrifying daylight attack at a Western Australian beach.

entries.title: Sticking to his guns! Harry is protected by armed bodyguards as he heads to The Late Show studio
entries.description: Prince Harry was in Manhattan on Monday to film an interview with Stephen Colbert. The interview will be broadcast on Tuesday night, as part of Harry's media tour to promote his memoir.

entries.title: Sydney's north shore Cammeray Mosman Neutral Bay Olympic Park spooked by 'creepy' rumbling noise
entries.description: Locals from upmarket Mosman and Kirribilli on the lower north shore over to Olympic Park in the inner west and out to the north-west all reported hearing the strange sounds on Monday night.

entries.title: Marjorie Taylor Greene takes on Dr. Dre after using rap riff in video
entries.description: Firebrand Republican Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene slammed rapper Dr. Dre Monday after he took her on for using a riff of his music in a video promoting the new House Republican majority.

entries.title: Administration won't force Bolsonaro to leave Florida while he is in hospital; Lula to visit DC
entries.description: Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro, who has been living in Florida, won't be sent home by the U.S. while he is hospitalized near Orlando after experiencing 'abdominal pains.'

entries.title: Child plunges 10m from balcony in Mount Druitt, in Sydney's west, as helicopter rushes to scene
entries.description: A child has been rushed to hospital after plunging 10m from an apartment balcony on Hythe Street in Mount Druitt, in Sydney's west this morning.

entries.title: Elgin Marbles should remain in Britain because they will be 'better preserved', Greek academic says
entries.description: Under plans drawn up by British Museum chairman George Osborne, the Elgin Marbles could soon be sent back to Greece. But a former Athens City Museum director says they should remain in London.

entries.title: SatanCon2023 is dedicated to Boston Mayor Michelle Wu after Satanic Temple was barred
entries.description: The Satanic Temple is planning to hold 'SatanCon 2023' which it describes as the 'largest satanic gathering in history,' in downtown Boston April 28-30.
